==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Purfle
<hw>Pur"fle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>pourfiler</ets>; <ets>pour</ets> for + <ets>fil</ets> a thread, L.
<ets>filum</ets>. See <er>Profile</er>, and cf. <er>Purl</er> a
border.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To decorate with a wrought or flowered
border; to embroider; to ornament with metallic threads; <as>as, to
<ex>purfle</ex> with blue and white</as>.</def> <rj><au>P.
Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A goodly lady clad in scarlet red,⟦br⟧
<qex>Purfled</qex> with gold and pearl of rich assay.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>To ornament with a bordure of
emines, furs, and the like; also, with gold studs or
mountings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Purflew</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Purfle</ent>⟦br⟧
